sub_title: Senior at KPMG Netherlands | Post-Master graduate
summary:
Son of a family business passionate about flower bulbs, teamwork, and international opportunities. After my Finance and Accounting studies at the University of Amsterdam, Jönköping University (Sweden) crossed my path for one outstanding Erasmus-Exchange semester learning about Digitalisation, Entrepreneurship and Sustainability. Looking for more cultural experiences, I have studied Chinese for 3 unique months at the Hutong School in Shanghai while living with a Chinese family. 
Joined KPMG Audit last September.

Interested in many topics, from local agriculture to international business, from capital markets to sustainability, and from digitalization to bridging cultural differences. 

Keen for a better future.
